open Git Bash
input cd to the home directory 
then 
    touch .bashrc
    vim .bashrc
input the change you want in this file
note the right grammer
then 
    source .bashrc


Example:
Add "man" into Git Bash
    cd
    touch .bashrc
    vim .bashrc
        man(){ $1 ==help; }
    source .bashrc
Then you can use the "man" in your git bash